article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 70, Indiana St. 58
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Nathan Peavy scored 21 points on 7-of-11 shooting to lead Miami of Ohio to a 70-58 victory over Indiana State on Saturday. Tim Pollitz had 20 points and Eric Bramos added 13 points for the Redhawks (13-12). Gabe Moore led Indiana State (12-15) with 15 points and eight assists. Trent Wurtz added 11 points for the Sycamores in their fourth straight loss. Wurtz's layup with 4:02 left in the first half capped a 10-0 run for the Sycamores and gave them their largest lead of 10 points. Miami trailed 38-31 at halftime, but went on a 13-1 run over the first 8:26 of the second half to take a 44-39 lead with 11:34 remaining. The Redhawks shot 12-of-23 (52 percent) from the floor in the second half and held the Sycamores to 6-of-25 (24 percent) shooting.
